			"typeName": "shape"
		},
		{
			"x": 1218.5448691092752,
			"y": 1447.7720975324762,
			"rotation": 0,
			"isLocked": false,
			"opacity": 1,
			"meta": {},
			"id": "shape:HWwmhiws8qA3jHLHnpTCT",
			"type": "text",
			"props": {
				"color": "black",
				"size": "xl",
				"w": 3762.8519976364914,
				"text": "what is vps  ?\nAllows you to run your services in a remote data center.\nVPS aka DropLet. small virtual Linux machine that is provided by a large cloud service that manages\ndata centers full of servers, networking equipment, and storage systems — and rents \nthem to you on-demand.\n\nSo when you create a Droplet in DigitalOcean, you’re:\nAsking DigitalOcean to run a virtual machine inside one of their physical servers,\nIn a specific data center region (e.g., Frankfurt, Amsterdam, New York).",
				"font": "serif",
				"textAlign": "start",
				"autoSize": true,
				"scale": 1.7872066958228356
			},
			"parentId": "page:page",
			"index": "aF2e1",
			"typeName": "shape"
		},
		{
			"x": -239.78861357322376,
			"y": 3539.0111540360945,
			"rotation": 0,
			"isLocked": false,
			"opacity": 1,
			"meta": {},
			"id": "shape:ove2BiA_ImNZZwzqulNC8",
			"type": "text",
			"props": {
				"color": "black",
				"size": "xl",
				"w": 2616.671875,
				"text": "A data center is a physical location where thousands (or millions) of servers are stored and managed.\n\nThink of it like a warehouse of computers, connected with high-speed internet, power backup, cooling systems, and security.\n\nCloud providers put their servers in these data centers and then virtualize them so you can rent a piece (a VPS) remotely.",
				"font": "serif",
				"textAlign": "middle",
				"autoSize": true,
				"scale": 1
			},
			"parentId": "page:page",
			"index": "aG6Pi",
			"typeName": "shape"
		},
